g.title: j1689619872
g.text: I have to ask you something and I don’t think you’re going to like it. I think you must have known deep down that this conversation would have to happen one day, given my condition.

g.title: j3258390683
g.text: I trust you, and I like you, so I’m just going to come out with it, okay?

g.title: j4018386182
g.text: I have no right to ask, really, but I need to know.

g.title: j1169452303
g.text: If I turned, completely - if the Techrot took me and I wasn’t the Eleanor you knew any more - would you kill me?

g.title: j3192931553
g.text: Would you want me to?

g.title: j2223552047
g.text: Sure.

g.title: j1623411080
g.text: Never.

g.title: j3160073708
g.text: I’m not going to answer that.

g.title: j3172852104
g.text: Hmm. Good start. You’ve made it about what I want instead of seeing my life as an opportunity to flex your personal morals. You just let me know that this isn’t about you.

g.title: j427662113
g.text: Wow. Okay.

g.title: j2047383860
g.text: Okay. Um.

g.title: j3147148465
g.text: As you wish.

g.title: j3515225002
g.text: That’s rare.

g.title: j2575160322
g.text: No hesitation, no struggle, just a simple yes.

g.title: j2446230930
g.text: Sorry. I'm actually a little overwhelmed. I didn't expect you to be that forthright.

g.title: j3833306555
g.text: I won't ask again.

g.title: j4164368750
g.text: Unfortunately it doesn’t get us out of our dilemma, because it means I never get to change my mind.

g.title: j1748261362
g.text: Thank you. You're an enigma to me in many ways, but now I know you'd be willing to put a bullet through my head, and that sort of thing is important in the workplace.

g.title: j3950696065
g.text: You'd let the monster live?

g.title: j1665958902
g.text: I suppose we'll have to wait until it happens to see how you react, won't we?

g.title: j2088564448
g.text: Let’s say I say yes, I’d want you to end me quick and clean rather than for me to go on living as a ravening freak. Let’s say that’s what Eleanor wants NOW.

g.title: j2573372251
g.text: Aaaand I just felt the Techrot in my cells give an anxious little quiver.

g.title: j1483813627
g.text: Sorry, sorry, it's just that I've been living every day with Lettie in my ear crowing about how I don't deserve to be here and Arthur looking at me like I'm a lost cause and he's counting the days till he has to do it, and I just didn't expect you to say that ok

g.title: j2356848020
g.text: You're a lethal little enigma.

g.title: j354582419
g.text: But what if the ravening freak is me, only more so? What if, once my humanity burns away in the Techrot crucible, I don’t WANT to die?

g.title: j2640670813
g.text: I think it's going to behave itself a little better from now on. Nothing like threatening the host to put the fear of Sol into the parasite, eh?

g.title: j102151550
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j1666653403
g.text: And so am I.

g.title: j1400832113
g.text: Because it makes me feel alive, Drifter. Powerfully alive.

g.title: j2864742878
g.text: Boolean EleanorNoDate is now true.

g.title: j1638332379
g.text: Crying. Happy tears. Talk soon. Please

g.title: j3083875712
g.text: I’d still do it.

g.title: j219772675
g.text: Point taken. I wouldn’t do it.

g.title: j643338225
g.text: It would depend on how many other people would be endangered.

g.title: j355790175
g.text: You haven’t answered the question. Would you want me to?

j3667248997
g.text: Okay. So we're sacrificing happy, empowered Eleanor on the altar of Eleanor as she used to be?

g.title: j536531278
g.text: Oh, so all I'd need to do is blink my big beautiful eyes at you and your resolve would crumble?

g.title: j561047826
g.text: Ah. Right. In this scenario, I’m an inhuman monster who’s presumably slaughtering people willy-nilly. You get to put me in the ‘predatory animal’ category, along with rabid dogs and hungry bears and such, which means there’s no moral quandary.

g.title: j3156770273
g.text: … I don’t know. Some days I think so. I feel like the stock character from a melodrama.

g.title: j838446618
g.text: I can change my mind and decide to live, but you can't change yours?

g.title: j4046823177
g.text: What kind of fearless vampire killer would you be then?

g.title: j2053665399
g.text: So tell me.

g.title: j1582498667
g.text: “Oh no, the hapless girl we once loved has become a sexy vampire. Let us kill her so that in death she will become pure and innocent once again.”

g.title: j4013698080
g.text: I shouldn't be surprised. It's the ending the stories prepare you for.

g.title: j182891706
g.text: I'll tell you. You'll be the kind who dies halfway through the movie, because they didn't have the heart to Do What Had To Be Done.

g.title: j4007580257
g.text: Do you wait until I claim my first victim before you pop a bullet through my skull?

g.title: j3409646822
g.text: Boolean EleanorArthurNightmare is now true.

g.title: j721312232
g.text: “Oh no, the hapless girl we once loved has become a sexy vampire. Let us kill her so that in death she will become pure and innocent once again.”

g.title: j2962050602
g.text: You'll be a warning to the others, you will!

g.title: j1437701255
g.text: Because if you don’t, how can you be sure I’m a danger?

g.title: j3919130302
g.text: I obsessed over it, actually. I had nightmares where I’d wake up on my couch and Arthur would be standing over me, tears in his eyes and sword in his hand, and he’d grate out some line about how Eleanor was his sister but now Eleanor was GONE, and he had to do this even though it was killing him, boo hoo.

g.title: j1238887557
g.text: Boolean EleanorArthurNightmare is now true.

g.title: j2173053205
g.text: Sorry. I'm not being very fair with you. Talk soon.

g.title: j2654325905
g.text: And as he shoves the blade between my ribs I’m screaming “Eleanor is RIGHT HERE, you stupid bastard!” but he can’t hear me any more.

g.title: j1966969496
g.text: In which case, you can’t expect me to, either.

g.title: j127552117
g.text: Maybe I'll dream about you next.
